{"id":29073,"title":"[Suicidal drug overdose while receiving palliative home care: a case report].","abstract":"Suicidal thoughts are a common phenomenon in palliative care which can be seen in around 10% of the patients. There is very little knowledge about attempted and committed suicide. This article is a case report about a patient with lung cancer in a terminal state of illness who ingested drugs in a toxic dose while receiving palliative home care. This article deals with ethical issues in medical treatment and various ways of decision-making.","date":"2014-05-22","categories":"Chemically-Induced Disorders","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24733303","annotations":[{"name":"Lung cancer","weight":0.850337,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lung_cancer"},{"name":"Cancer","weight":0.801843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.801843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Suicide","weight":0.784197,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suicide"},{"name":"Lung","weight":0.783378,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lung"},{"name":"Medicine","weight":0.754651,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medicine"},{"name":"Drug","weight":0.743484,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug"},{"name":"Toxicity","weight":0.73221,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toxicity"},{"name":"Palliative care","weight":0.724397,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palliative_care"},{"name":"Illness","weight":0.716476,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Illness"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.683991,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Suicidal ideation","weight":0.68318,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suicidal_ideation"},{"name":"Ethics","weight":0.673266,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethics"},{"name":"Drug over